default6.0 defaultPublic service broadcastingdefault&#xa0;
default6.1 The current scale of public service broadcasting is inappropriate in the digital age.  There is no
default longer any
default justification for funding popular entertainment programmes from a
default flat rate
default 
defaultTV 
defaultlicensing system enforced by the criminal law. The media market should be used to
default fund these 
defaultpopular 
defaultprogrammes through voluntary subscriptions.
default&#xa0;
default6.2 The scope and quantity of public service broadcasting should be reviewed
default.  Fixed term contracts for public
default service
default 
defaultbroadcasting should then be allocated by a public broadcasting authority to a
default range of
default reputable broadcaster
defaults who are 
defaultwilling to provide content that the market 
defaultwill not fund.
default&#xa0;
default6.3 Public service broadcasting should be funded from general taxation
default at a level agreed annually by Parliament.
